00:18:26.281 --> 00:18:32.288
transaction which centers on
Spain but involves several

00:18:32.288 --> 00:18:35.960
European countries at once.
 

00:18:35.960 --> 00:19:14.690
 
 

00:19:14.690 --> 00:19:20.844
Paolo Zanonni:
 Let me try to look at one

00:19:20.844 --> 00:19:28.568
case, which is actually--let's
take it one step backward.

00:19:28.568 --> 00:19:33.518
The case I would like to
discuss is the attempt by the

00:19:33.518 --> 00:19:37.720
new management of a large
utility company,

00:19:37.720 --> 00:19:43.182
Enel, which is only electrical,
but not the only electrical

00:19:43.182 --> 00:19:49.215
utility company in Italy,
to change the structure and the

00:19:49.215 --> 00:19:53.598
characteristic of the company
totally,

00:19:53.598 --> 00:19:59.492
and the attempt by the
management over a period of six

00:19:59.492 --> 00:20:06.387
or seven years to turn a major
utility company depending mostly

00:20:06.387 --> 00:20:12.479
on one single nation,
into a different company that

00:20:12.479 --> 00:20:19.430
will diminish the risk by being
present into several nations,

00:20:19.430 --> 00:20:24.328
but at the same time,
that will totally change the

00:20:24.328 --> 00:20:27.630
characteristic of that company.
 

00:20:27.630 --> 00:20:29.740
Let me try to explain.
 

00:20:29.740 --> 00:20:35.627
If you take a utility,
usually utility has very little

00:20:35.627 --> 00:20:40.740
risk because it lives in a
regulated sector.

00:20:40.740 --> 00:20:46.220
It makes--it has an agreement
with a regulator that the

00:20:46.220 --> 00:20:52.063
utility will may--
would make certain level of

00:20:52.063 --> 00:20:57.656
capital investment,
and in exchange,

00:20:57.656 --> 00:21:06.358
will be able to impose on the
customer some tariffs.

00:21:06.358 --> 00:21:11.615
If you can imagine,
utilities would be a very,

00:21:11.615 --> 00:21:16.637
very safe investment for the
small investor,

00:21:16.637 --> 00:21:20.608
it would be similar to a bond.
 

00:21:20.608 --> 00:21:24.394
You have to do capital
investment, because capital

00:21:24.394 --> 00:21:28.410
investments are a reward through
a tariff system,

00:21:28.410 --> 00:21:31.520
and if you invest in the
company it's like investing in a

00:21:31.520 --> 00:21:31.910
bond.
 

00:21:31.910 --> 00:21:35.921
If you look at utilities,
have small capital

00:21:35.921 --> 00:21:39.558
appreciation,
and pay high dividends.

00:21:39.558 --> 00:21:43.105
The new management of Enel,
when Enel was sort of

00:21:43.105 --> 00:21:46.650
privatized,
decided that they were trying

00:21:46.650 --> 00:21:51.929
to change that completely and
tried to make the boring utility

00:21:51.929 --> 00:21:56.690
into a company that was going to
offer more growth,

00:21:56.690 --> 00:22:04.900
more risk, less dividend,
and more capital appreciation.

00:22:04.900 --> 00:22:08.670
When you try to do that
to--with a giant--

00:22:08.670 --> 00:22:11.665
that at the time that they
decided to do it I think that

00:22:11.665 --> 00:22:13.900
Enel was worth about 40 billion
Euros,

00:22:13.900 --> 00:22:17.619
which would make it $60 billion
dollars at today's exchange

00:22:17.619 --> 00:22:18.069
rate.
 

00:22:18.069 --> 00:22:22.618
It's a major task.
 

00:22:22.618 --> 00:22:30.142
The way the management decided
to do it was through changing

00:22:30.142 --> 00:22:36.900
the product mix and getting into
renewable energy,

00:22:36.900 --> 00:22:43.259
but also in trying to start the
policy of aggressive

00:22:43.259 --> 00:22:48.890
diversification,
moving into other countries.

00:22:48.890 --> 00:22:52.990
First they moved into Eastern
Europe,

00:22:52.990 --> 00:22:59.344
to some extent and Russia,
but one thing that you learn

00:22:59.344 --> 00:23:06.640
when you take the helm of a $60
billion dollar corporation,

00:23:06.640 --> 00:23:13.190
is that if you try to change
the characteristic of the

00:23:13.190 --> 00:23:19.000
company by a set of small size
acquisitions,

00:23:19.000 --> 00:23:22.106
you run out of time,
because if you are a

00:23:22.106 --> 00:23:25.901
professional--
if you have a professional

00:23:25.901 --> 00:23:30.960
management team executing--
execute, making and executing a

00:23:30.960 --> 00:23:34.138
small deal,
it takes as much time and

00:23:34.138 --> 00:23:37.318
effort in as executing a huge
one,

00:23:37.318 --> 00:23:42.348
and so what is different is the
amount of risk.

00:23:42.348 --> 00:23:48.973
So the management of Enel
starts looking around at one

00:23:48.973 --> 00:23:56.598
single move that would have
changed the company completely.

00:23:56.598 --> 00:24:02.650
One of the areas in the nations
where they looked at was Spain.

00:24:02.650 --> 00:24:04.940
Why it was Spain?
 

00:24:04.940 --> 00:24:12.824
First, Spain has a first
rate--as generally has a first

00:24:12.824 --> 00:24:19.698
rate public elite,
it's usually--I would say it's

00:24:19.698 --> 00:24:25.028
a country where their regulatory
system,

00:24:25.028 --> 00:24:29.818
especially for utilities,
it's very good,

00:24:29.818 --> 00:24:33.950
it's very stable,
it's well regulated,

00:24:33.950 --> 00:24:42.598
there is a centuries old
structure of tariff--

00:24:42.598 --> 00:24:45.410
regulation and tariff behavior
that is very good,

00:24:45.410 --> 00:24:48.538
and this has created as you can
see,

00:24:48.538 --> 00:24:52.440
in a country that is really
small or reasonably small,

00:24:52.440 --> 00:25:01.306
the presence of at least five
or six utilities that are of a

00:25:01.306 --> 00:25:03.410
decent size.
 

00:25:03.410 --> 00:25:10.083
So there was--there is room for
consolidation in America that is

00:25:10.083 --> 00:25:15.380
very attractive from the
economic point of view.

00:25:15.380 --> 00:25:22.431
Obviously Spain was one of the
first nations where the Enel

00:25:22.431 --> 00:25:27.767
management looked at,
moreover as you can see,

00:25:27.767 --> 00:25:33.911
it's true there are six players
but when you go to electricity

00:25:33.911 --> 00:25:39.349
you only have two players that
are very important,

00:25:39.349 --> 00:25:43.029
Endesa and Iberdrola.
 

00:25:43.029 --> 00:25:51.096
So Enel--the management of Enel
paid very close attention to the

00:25:51.096 --> 00:25:57.884
development in the Spanish
market and to opportunities

00:25:57.884 --> 00:26:02.750
opening up in the Spanish
markets.

00:26:02.750 --> 00:26:07.190
What happened at one point was
that--

00:26:07.190 --> 00:26:10.090
I don't know how familiar you
are with Spanish as a political

00:26:10.090 --> 00:26:15.575
economic system,
so let me step back for one

00:26:15.575 --> 00:26:21.009
second and give you a few--
you can ask questions.

00:26:21.009 --> 00:26:23.571
By the way, you can interrupt
and ask questions any time you

00:26:23.571 --> 00:26:24.508
want,
because if not,

00:26:24.508 --> 00:26:29.152
this gets very boring,
because it's very confusing

00:26:29.152 --> 00:26:31.618
possibly as well.
 

00:26:31.618 --> 00:26:37.477
A Spanish political economic
system from the political point

00:26:37.477 --> 00:26:42.988
of view,
it's a very stable democracy,

00:26:42.988 --> 00:26:49.538
where you tend to have two
large parties,

00:26:49.538 --> 00:26:53.500
that usually occupy the
government for some--

00:26:53.500 --> 00:27:00.319
for a reasonable amount--for a
reasonably long time and change

00:27:00.319 --> 00:27:02.681
orderly,
and there's the division

00:27:02.681 --> 00:27:03.858
between the two parties.
 

00:27:03.858 --> 00:27:08.558
One is a conservative parties
linked with,

00:27:08.558 --> 00:27:13.436
to some extent,
linked with the old Catholic

00:27:13.436 --> 00:27:19.311
heritage of Spain,
and the other is a democratic

00:27:19.311 --> 00:27:23.178
socialist party,
more or less linked with the

00:27:23.178 --> 00:27:26.930
socialist heritages of Spain,
which is also significant.

00:27:26.930 --> 00:27:31.111
I don't know how many of you
are--well I suppose most of you

00:27:31.111 --> 00:27:35.009
are familiar with the Spanish
Civil War of 1975-1977.

00:27:35.009 --> 00:27:41.864
At the same time these two
parties live in a culture where

00:27:41.864 --> 00:27:47.996
regional differences and
regional cleavages are very

00:27:47.996 --> 00:27:49.680
important.
 

00:27:49.680 --> 00:27:52.673
These are the main
characteristic of the Spain--of

00:27:52.673 --> 00:27:55.952
the political system;
we'll come to the economic

00:27:55.952 --> 00:27:59.262
system in a while,
so two large groups strongly

00:27:59.262 --> 00:28:03.440
identified with the two main
traditions in the country.

00:28:03.440 --> 00:28:10.150
One is socialist and the other
is Catholic and having--

00:28:10.150 --> 00:28:14.712
also living in a situation in
which you have a high degree of

00:28:14.712 --> 00:28:18.058
differentiation between
different regions.

00:28:18.058 --> 00:28:22.190
Everybody knows about the
Basque areas,

00:28:22.190 --> 00:28:25.397
but at the same time,
you're also to consider that

00:28:25.397 --> 00:28:28.411
Catalonia,
the area where Barcelona is,

00:28:28.411 --> 00:28:32.368
had been striving for autonomy,
if not independence,

00:28:32.368 --> 00:28:33.920
for a very long time.
 

00:28:33.920 --> 00:28:35.761
These are the characteristics
of the political economic

00:28:35.761 --> 00:28:36.068
system.
 

00:28:36.068 --> 00:28:40.452
As far as the model of
development that Spain has

00:28:40.452 --> 00:28:43.021
followed,
especially in the last twenty

00:28:43.021 --> 00:28:47.057
to twenty-five years,
is a model of development that

00:28:47.057 --> 00:28:52.029
is largely biased toward
construction and real estate

00:28:52.029 --> 00:28:57.608
development,
and so-and very entrepreneurial.

00:28:57.608 --> 00:29:03.132
So you have--you have
especially in the late 1990s and

00:29:03.132 --> 00:29:08.250
in the early 2000,
the creation of a lot of very

00:29:08.250 --> 00:29:12.623
entrepreneurial,
very aggressive,

00:29:12.623 --> 00:29:19.442
very wealthy companies that--
which line of business were

00:29:19.442 --> 00:29:22.230
mostly construction and real
estate.

00:29:22.230 --> 00:29:24.150
The entrepreneurs in these
companies--

00:29:24.150 --> 00:29:28.528
you say what does that have to
do with utilities,

00:29:28.528 --> 00:29:32.348
and what does it have to do
with the opportunities open to

00:29:32.348 --> 00:29:35.029
Enel to enter into the Spanish
market?

00:29:35.029 --> 00:29:40.471
It has to do--as you can see,
one of the diversification

00:29:40.471 --> 00:29:45.616
policies used by these
entrepreneurial companies that

00:29:45.616 --> 00:29:51.750
have made most of the money on
real estate and construction was

00:29:51.750 --> 00:29:56.599
to buy stakes into large utility
companies.

00:29:56.599 --> 00:29:58.890
Why?
 

00:29:58.890 --> 00:30:02.170
It's a good diversification
policy.

00:30:02.170 --> 00:30:06.960
It pays stable dividends,
as we saw at the beginning,

00:30:06.960 --> 00:30:11.143
and plus you enter into an
industrial sector that is

00:30:11.143 --> 00:30:14.636
fractionalized,
and so assuming that there is

00:30:14.636 --> 00:30:16.558
consolidation,
&gt;

00:30:16.558 --> 00:30:19.327
or seven players,
you are likely to be paid a

00:30:19.327 --> 00:30:21.778
premium for the shares that you
have.

00:30:21.778 --> 00:30:24.200
So what I tried to do there is
very complex,

00:30:24.200 --> 00:30:27.220
and so you have to excuse me
and you have to ask questions,

00:30:27.220 --> 00:30:31.806
is that--this is different from
the utility sector in any

00:30:31.806 --> 00:30:35.578
country that I have--
that I know of.

00:30:35.578 --> 00:30:40.411
You have large,
or you had, large construction

00:30:40.411 --> 00:30:46.529
companies as minority but
significant shareholders in many

00:30:46.529 --> 00:30:50.608
of the utility companies in
Spain.

00:30:50.608 --> 00:30:53.848
They are there for two
reasons--for three reasons;

00:30:53.848 --> 00:30:59.090
diversification of risk because
you are in a very stable

00:30:59.090 --> 00:31:05.190
business, totally different from
construction and real estate.

00:31:05.190 --> 00:31:08.542
You get high dividends for the
stake that you have bought,

00:31:08.542 --> 00:31:11.250
and so you get a good yield on
your capital.

00:31:11.250 --> 00:31:14.895
Third, there is likely to be
consolidation and so you are

00:31:14.895 --> 00:31:19.130
likely to be paid a premium for
the shares that you purchased,

00:31:19.130 --> 00:31:22.900
so a very nice position to be
in.

00:31:22.900 --> 00:31:28.344
But look at this for a second,
in every company in which there

00:31:28.344 --> 00:31:30.348
is--
for the same reason that I

00:31:30.348 --> 00:31:33.712
tried to tell you,
every utility company where

00:31:33.712 --> 00:31:37.684
there is one of these
construction companies as a

00:31:37.684 --> 00:31:42.650
shareholder does not have a very
solid shareholder base,

00:31:42.650 --> 00:31:46.778
because one of the main
shareholders is there not

00:31:46.778 --> 00:31:52.368
because of commitment to that
particular industry or anything,

00:31:52.368 --> 00:31:56.645
but just for having built while
it lasts and for selling the

00:31:56.645 --> 00:32:00.269
shares at a premium when there
is consolidation.

00:32:00.269 --> 00:32:03.637
If you look from the point of
view of someone that wants to

00:32:03.637 --> 00:32:08.251
enter the market,
you have very attractive market

00:32:08.251 --> 00:32:14.490
because the regulatory regime is
very good and you have a

00:32:14.490 --> 00:32:20.950
situation of not totally stable
shareholder base in each of

00:32:20.950 --> 00:32:23.288
these countries.
 

00:32:23.288 --> 00:32:28.988
As everybody expected,
at the end of 2005,

00:32:28.988 --> 00:32:36.633
the fact that the structure of
the industry had too many

00:32:36.633 --> 00:32:41.220
players, it started changing.
 

00:32:41.220 --> 00:32:45.240
One of the companies,
Gas Natural,

00:32:45.240 --> 00:32:50.358
decided to launch an hostile
bid on Endesa,

00:32:50.358 --> 00:32:53.650
counting on two things.
 

00:32:53.650 --> 00:32:57.005
Counting on the fact that
Endesa, where the shareholder

00:32:57.005 --> 00:33:00.933
would have been the seller,
for the same reason that I gave

00:33:00.933 --> 00:33:04.384
you before,
and on the fact that where

00:33:04.384 --> 00:33:10.548
synergies and economies of scale
and scope that could have been

00:33:10.548 --> 00:33:16.316
achieved or implemented by
putting together Gas Natural and

00:33:16.316 --> 00:33:17.509
Endesa.
 

00:33:17.509 --> 00:33:22.361
They launched the hostile bid,
but something that they didn't

00:33:22.361 --> 00:33:29.663
count on happened immediately,
which is that the reactions to

00:33:29.663 --> 00:33:37.078
that bid was not very friendly
by two entities;

00:33:37.078 --> 00:33:42.102
the regulators,
as you can see the C&amp;E,

00:33:42.102 --> 00:33:45.568
and the Spanish government.
 

00:33:45.568 --> 00:33:52.480
Why was not the Spanish
government reaction favorable?

00:33:52.480 --> 00:33:57.277
First, you have a deal that
makes perfect sense from the

00:33:57.277 --> 00:34:00.680
economic and financial point of
view.

00:34:00.680 --> 00:34:04.821
The shareholders of Endesa are
happy because they get paid a

00:34:04.821 --> 00:34:10.023
decent premium on their stock,
the company remains Spanish,

00:34:10.023 --> 00:34:13.940
synergies are going to be
extracted,

00:34:13.940 --> 00:34:17.431
there is not a lot of
overlapping and so there are not

00:34:17.431 --> 00:34:21.489
going to be a lot of layoffs,
the ensuing company will be

00:34:21.489 --> 00:34:24.188
very strong,
will definitely be a national

00:34:24.188 --> 00:34:26.820
champion,
probably a European champion;

00:34:26.820 --> 00:34:30.679
so why doesn't the government
like it?

00:34:30.679 --> 00:34:42.242
It happens to be that Endesa is
Madrid based and Gas Natural is

00:34:42.242 --> 00:34:46.159
based on Barcelona.
 

00:34:46.159 --> 00:34:51.833
It also happens to be that at
the same time there is a big

00:34:51.833 --> 00:34:57.407
fight in the political arena
between the government party

00:34:57.407 --> 00:35:01.501
socialist,
and the opposition party,

00:35:01.501 --> 00:35:08.057
the conservative and one of the
issues that they are fighting on

00:35:08.057 --> 00:35:13.989
is decentralization of power
within different regions.

00:35:13.989 --> 00:35:19.385
It also happens that while a
large part of the power base of

00:35:19.385 --> 00:35:22.679
the socialist party is in
Madrid,

00:35:22.679 --> 00:35:28.014
a reasonably large base of the
power of the conservative party

00:35:28.014 --> 00:35:29.590
is in Barcelona.
 

00:35:29.590 --> 00:35:34.000
So oddly enough,
or naturally enough,

00:35:34.000 --> 00:35:42.132
the ruling socialist party sees
the attempt by a gas company

00:35:42.132 --> 00:35:48.199
from Barcelona to try to buy the
biggest,

00:35:48.199 --> 00:35:51.949
or one of, the second biggest,
depends on how you count,

00:35:51.949 --> 00:35:56.876
utility company based in
Madrid, as almost a political

00:35:56.876 --> 00:36:00.409
move instead of an industrial
move,

00:36:00.409 --> 00:36:02.329
and they just don't like it.
 

00:36:02.329 --> 00:36:04.994
And so they tried to stop it,
as you can see from the

00:36:04.994 --> 00:36:08.478
statement,
they tried to stop it making it

00:36:08.478 --> 00:36:13.751
difficult so the regulatory
agency and just trying to fight

00:36:13.751 --> 00:36:17.570
it with all the weapons that
they have.

00:36:17.570 --> 00:36:22.731
Enel, the Italian utility
company, has not been the only

00:36:22.731 --> 00:36:26.110
one looking at the Spanish
market.

00:36:26.110 --> 00:36:30.295
If the Spanish is that
attractive, as I tried to

00:36:30.295 --> 00:36:34.840
describe it to you that means
that someone else--

00:36:34.840 --> 00:36:38.829
a few other people have been
looking for opportunities to

00:36:38.829 --> 00:36:43.320
enter the Spanish market and get
hold of one of those prizes.

00:36:43.320 --> 00:36:50.141
One of the companies that's
been looking for that is the

00:36:50.141 --> 00:36:53.489
German giant called E.On.
 

00:36:53.489 --> 00:36:56.197
E.On is an exceedingly
sophisticated company,

00:36:56.197 --> 00:36:57.059
exceedingly.
 

00:36:57.059 --> 00:37:00.045
They are sophisticated,
they have been a leading

00:37:00.045 --> 00:37:04.389
utility for so many years,
they know all the complexities

00:37:04.389 --> 00:37:09.139
of operating in a regulated
sector where you depend on the

00:37:09.139 --> 00:37:12.389
investment you make in the
tariffs,

00:37:12.389 --> 00:37:16.733
so they are very sophisticated
in understanding the political

00:37:16.733 --> 00:37:19.340
environment in which you
operate,

00:37:19.340 --> 00:37:24.268
and which heavily influences
your outcome and your choices.

00:37:24.268 --> 00:37:27.568
They see an opening,
they say wait a second,

00:37:27.568 --> 00:37:31.710
and the government doesn't like
the Gas Natural bid.

00:37:31.710 --> 00:37:34.539
Gas Natural doesn't have a lot
of cash,

