so it will be difficult for
them to raise--

00:37:37.889 --> 00:37:40.489
it would be difficult for them
to raise the bid,

00:37:40.489 --> 00:37:44.682
at the same time,
they don't seem to have

00:37:44.682 --> 00:37:46.780
political support.
 

00:37:46.780 --> 00:37:52.702
So maybe here there is a space
for a foreign bidder that will

00:37:52.702 --> 00:37:58.824
table for the shareholders a bid
that is higher than the bid of

00:37:58.824 --> 00:38:01.489
Gas Natural for Endesa.
 

00:38:01.489 --> 00:38:06.130
Gutsy move, because if you look
at hostile bid,

00:38:06.130 --> 00:38:10.670
cross border in Europe,
in a regulated sector,

00:38:10.670 --> 00:38:14.099
I think this is the first one.
 

00:38:14.099 --> 00:38:19.378
Very gutsy move,
very well structured,

00:38:19.378 --> 00:38:24.230
very well done,
very well timed.

00:38:24.230 --> 00:38:26.972
E.On moves, and,
as you noticed,

00:38:26.972 --> 00:38:31.929
the bid is significantly higher
than the previous one;

00:38:31.929 --> 00:38:38.489
€27 instead of €21.
 

00:38:38.489 --> 00:38:44.876
In a very sophisticated way,
which is worse if the company

00:38:44.876 --> 00:38:50.280
that E.On is,
they also start a sophisticated

00:38:50.280 --> 00:38:56.572
lobby with the European
Commission because they believe

00:38:56.572 --> 00:39:02.139
that the main threat;
it is not another bidder.

00:39:02.139 --> 00:39:06.989
The main threat is the Spanish
Government doesn't want a German

00:39:06.989 --> 00:39:10.510
utility own the leading champion
in Madrid.

00:39:10.510 --> 00:39:13.251
There's no reason why,
if they didn't like Barcelona

00:39:13.251 --> 00:39:15.407
to own it,
why shouldn't like--I don't

00:39:15.407 --> 00:39:17.947
remember what year it's based,
it's based in the

00:39:17.947 --> 00:39:19.460
&gt;
 

00:39:19.460 --> 00:39:24.150
somewhere, but I don't
remember, I think it's near

00:39:24.150 --> 00:39:26.498
Frankfurt, but--
Student:  It's

00:39:26.498 --> 00:39:26.800
Dusseldorf.
 

00:39:26.800 --> 00:39:28.628
Paolo Zanonni:
 Dusseldorf,

00:39:28.628 --> 00:39:30.570
sorry, you are right I was
wrong.

00:39:30.570 --> 00:39:35.672
E.On starts lobbying the
European Commission and hopes to

00:39:35.672 --> 00:39:39.590
have an opening by the German
regulators.

00:39:39.590 --> 00:39:44.659
An opening, really no bigger
position comes,

00:39:44.659 --> 00:39:51.853
but an opening really doesn't
come, and the Spanish government

00:39:51.853 --> 00:39:54.920
stalls, so rightly so.
 

00:39:54.920 --> 00:39:59.695
E.On looks at the ownership
structure of Endesa and sees

00:39:59.695 --> 00:40:02.650
that there are a lot of sellers.
 

00:40:02.650 --> 00:40:06.570
It says, "Okay this is
going to be a financial fight,

00:40:06.570 --> 00:40:13.889
let me just up the ante,
I raise my bid to €34 per

00:40:13.889 --> 00:40:18.739
share,
significantly higher than the

00:40:18.739 --> 00:40:24.768
offer by Gas Natural,
and they think that they have a

00:40:24.768 --> 00:40:26.190
winning hand.
 

00:40:26.190 --> 00:40:28.159
In addition,
they have all the resources.

00:40:28.159 --> 00:40:32.251
I think that it--I seem to
remember that at that time E.On

00:40:32.251 --> 00:40:36.630
has cash on the balance sheet
for about €100 billion--

00:40:36.630 --> 00:40:43.030
it's going to cost about $40 or
$42 billion?

00:40:43.030 --> 00:40:49.570
Again, they don't go anywhere
and they get stalled,

00:40:49.570 --> 00:40:55.067
at that point,
Enel, that has been watching

00:40:55.067 --> 00:41:00.170
the situation,
sees an opportunity.

00:41:00.170 --> 00:41:06.992
There is a bid by Gas Natural
that doesn't seem to go anywhere

00:41:06.992 --> 00:41:13.480
because of political opposition,
and because it's cheap.

00:41:13.480 --> 00:41:17.909
There is a bid by the leading
European champion,

00:41:17.909 --> 00:41:23.260
a utility, that is a lot richer
and can become a lot richer,

00:41:23.260 --> 00:41:29.199
but doesn't go anywhere because
the Spanish government is

00:41:29.199 --> 00:41:34.610
reluctant to sell or to have one
of the utility--

00:41:34.610 --> 00:41:41.550
one of the national champions
end up in German hands.

00:41:41.550 --> 00:41:48.313
Enel sees an opening and a
strategy based on three

00:41:48.313 --> 00:41:49.969
variables.
 

00:41:49.969 --> 00:41:56.268
One they say,
maybe we can pay as much as

00:41:56.268 --> 00:42:00.666
E.On,
we don't have the same cash on

00:42:00.666 --> 00:42:04.849
the balance sheet but we have no
debt,

00:42:04.849 --> 00:42:10.079
so we can try to fight it on
that.

00:42:10.079 --> 00:42:17.010
Second, is we might be more
acceptable to the Spanish

00:42:17.010 --> 00:42:23.010
government and that needs to be
found out,

00:42:23.010 --> 00:42:25.577
and the third is,
and this is really in my

00:42:25.577 --> 00:42:29.005
opinion the winning--
this is really the winning

00:42:29.005 --> 00:42:33.398
perception of Enel,
they say why should we buy off

00:42:33.398 --> 00:42:38.097
those construction companies,
for the biggest construction

00:42:38.097 --> 00:42:41.929
company that are--
that is in the capital.

00:42:41.929 --> 00:42:48.539
That can be our ally in
unlocking the situation.

00:42:48.539 --> 00:42:53.119
Why should we try to buy them
out?

00:42:53.119 --> 00:42:57.360
Why don't we simply go and talk
to the entrepreneur--

00:42:57.360 --> 00:43:00.936
this construction is usually
one entrepreneur for each

00:43:00.936 --> 00:43:03.442
company,
why don't we go and talk to the

00:43:03.442 --> 00:43:05.659
entrepreneur and see what do you
want.

00:43:05.659 --> 00:43:06.769
You want cash?
 

00:43:06.769 --> 00:43:07.760
We'll give it to you.
 

00:43:07.760 --> 00:43:11.257
If you want a piece of the
company, we will make a deal

00:43:11.257 --> 00:43:11.969
with you.
 

00:43:11.969 --> 00:43:13.880
What do you want?
 

00:43:13.880 --> 00:43:18.440
Oddly--naturally,
now the entrepreneur says,

00:43:18.440 --> 00:43:21.369
"No, no,
no the reason why I'm here is

00:43:21.369 --> 00:43:24.090
because I want to diversify my
risk,

00:43:24.090 --> 00:43:28.340
I want significant
opportunities to growth--

00:43:28.340 --> 00:43:33.327
to grow and so what I really
want is not cash but is a piece

00:43:33.327 --> 00:43:34.849
of Endesa."
 

00:43:34.849 --> 00:43:44.568
Enel says, okay let's discuss,
rationally now the

00:43:44.568 --> 00:43:50.641
entrepreneur,
which is Acciona,

00:43:50.641 --> 00:43:52.869
stalls.
 

00:43:52.869 --> 00:43:57.099
Enel tried to force his hand
does something very unusual.

00:43:57.099 --> 00:44:01.789
In very, very unusual in a
cross border takeover company,

00:44:01.789 --> 00:44:07.739
goes into the market,
and buys 10% of Endesa in the

00:44:07.739 --> 00:44:11.139
market,
which according to Spanish

00:44:11.139 --> 00:44:15.615
regulation you can do,
and Enel has not launched a bid

00:44:15.615 --> 00:44:16.010
yet.
 

00:44:16.010 --> 00:44:18.219
It's someone coming out of the
left field,

00:44:18.219 --> 00:44:23.179
so they go into the market and
they buy 10%,

00:44:23.179 --> 00:44:30.596
€39 per share,
higher than the bid for the bid

00:44:30.596 --> 00:44:32.079
by E.On.
 

00:44:32.079 --> 00:44:35.155
At that point they sit around
the table with the entrepreneur

00:44:35.155 --> 00:44:39.159
and say,
"See, we are very serious,

00:44:39.159 --> 00:44:43.695
so we are either going--either
we are going to buy this company

00:44:43.695 --> 00:44:50.996
or E.On is going to buy it,
or we make a deal and together

00:44:50.996 --> 00:44:53.889
we buy it."
 

00:44:53.889 --> 00:44:59.929
Long negotiations start with
the entrepreneur,

00:44:59.929 --> 00:45:04.831
and at the end,
a deal in this negotiation Enel

00:45:04.831 --> 00:45:07.568
again--
the entrepreneur stalls again

00:45:07.568 --> 00:45:11.393
or tried to get more,
so Enel again decides to be

00:45:11.393 --> 00:45:16.398
aggressive and does an equity
swap for a remaining 14% or

00:45:16.398 --> 00:45:21.494
14.99% of the capital which is
the maximum permitted under

00:45:21.494 --> 00:45:23.639
Spanish regulation.
 

00:45:23.639 --> 00:45:27.750
It tells the entrepreneur,
"See we are here to stay,

00:45:27.750 --> 00:45:32.420
we now own 25% of the company,
we own more than you do,

00:45:32.420 --> 00:45:33.809
and you will not get rid of us.
 

00:45:33.809 --> 00:45:38.878
At the same time they show E.On
that they own 25% and so that

00:45:38.878 --> 00:45:43.610
they are possibly in a position
to block the takeover.

00:45:43.610 --> 00:45:47.730
So this is a battle being
fought with two fronts.

00:45:47.730 --> 00:45:52.201
One, the only opportunity to
win, Enel rightly decides is to

00:45:52.201 --> 00:45:54.929
make a deal with the
entrepreneur;

00:45:54.929 --> 00:46:02.945
and two at the same time they
have to fight the offer by E.On

00:46:02.945 --> 00:46:08.956
which, as you can see,
increases this offer to

00:46:08.956 --> 00:46:12.030
€40 per share.
 

00:46:12.030 --> 00:46:17.344
At the same time,
Enel has been negotiating with

00:46:17.344 --> 00:46:24.353
entrepreneur and they strike a
deal in which 25% is going to be

00:46:24.353 --> 00:46:30.157
owned directly by Enel,
but 51% of the shares are going

00:46:30.157 --> 00:46:35.096
to be owned by a joint venture
company made by Enel and the

00:46:35.096 --> 00:46:40.668
entrepreneur who is Acciona,
where the entrepreneur has 51%,

00:46:40.668 --> 00:46:45.996
and the entrepreneur who is
scared about being trapped into

00:46:45.996 --> 00:46:50.039
a situation that is not liquid
also has--

00:46:50.039 --> 00:46:52.690
also negotiate with Enel,
a right of put,

00:46:52.690 --> 00:46:59.320
to put to Enel his own shares
for--his own shares in Endesa,

00:46:59.320 --> 00:47:03.539
for the same price that it has
been negotiated,

00:47:03.539 --> 00:47:07.710
the €41 per share.
 

00:47:07.710 --> 00:47:10.489
As you have seen--sorry I moved
it--

00:47:10.489 --> 00:47:18.139
as you have seen the final
battle is won by Enel,

00:47:18.139 --> 00:47:21.396
it made a deal with E.On on the
side in which E.On is going to

00:47:21.396 --> 00:47:23.639
be sold about $10 billion dollar
asset,

00:47:23.639 --> 00:47:27.807
€10 billion asset and so
E.On also gets a foothold in the

00:47:27.807 --> 00:47:31.840
Spanish market but Endesa stays
more or less what it is,

00:47:31.840 --> 00:47:35.789
and the situation is Enel,
Acciona,

00:47:35.789 --> 00:47:45.030
with Acciona has a right of put
to Enel for the shares that they

00:47:45.030 --> 00:47:45.909
own.
 

00:47:45.909 --> 00:47:48.268
Am I going too fast?
 

00:47:48.268 --> 00:47:50.858
Prof: You're doing fine,
but you've only got about three

00:47:50.858 --> 00:47:51.820
or four minutes left.
 

00:47:51.820 --> 00:47:55.380
Paolo Zanonni:
 I know but the rest is

00:47:55.380 --> 00:47:57.079
just the end of it.
 

00:47:57.079 --> 00:48:03.277
The situation is that the
Endesa/E.On folds,

00:48:03.277 --> 00:48:09.909
and Endesa is now owned by Enel
and Acciona.

00:48:09.909 --> 00:48:15.210
Now in the meantime,
what happens in the world--

00:48:15.210 --> 00:48:20.840
and what happens is that there
is a credit crunch,

00:48:20.840 --> 00:48:29.032
which, in the case of Spain,
overlaps with a very severe

00:48:29.032 --> 00:48:35.440
downturn in construction and
real estate.

00:48:35.440 --> 00:48:40.492
You have--we need to
differentiate here between

00:48:40.492 --> 00:48:42.909
different countries.
 

00:48:42.909 --> 00:48:47.090
You have to think that the
reliance on debt and the

00:48:47.090 --> 00:48:50.768
reliance on construction and
real estate,

00:48:50.768 --> 00:48:56.128
in the case of Spain,
was so high that while in

00:48:56.128 --> 00:49:03.119
Europe you have an unemployment
rate that is below 10% and in

00:49:03.119 --> 00:49:07.780
the states you have one that is
10%.

00:49:07.780 --> 00:49:14.594
In Spain you have an
unemployment rate which is 24%,

00:49:14.594 --> 00:49:17.000
if well counted.
 

00:49:17.000 --> 00:49:22.664
The whole model of development
of the Spanish economy is in

00:49:22.664 --> 00:49:27.936
doubt, or is in crisis,
because of the severe crisis in

00:49:27.936 --> 00:49:31.159
construction and real estate.
 

00:49:31.159 --> 00:49:35.509
It's easier to add that most of
the companies that have been

00:49:35.509 --> 00:49:38.800
operating there,
including Acciona,

00:49:38.800 --> 00:49:44.994
the partner of E.On had been
buying shares with loans by the

00:49:44.994 --> 00:49:46.780
Spanish banks.
 

00:49:46.780 --> 00:49:51.389
Not only you have the collapse
in the prices of the real estate

00:49:51.389 --> 00:49:54.130
asset,
you have also the trouble in

00:49:54.130 --> 00:49:56.940
refinancing the loan that have
been--

00:49:56.940 --> 00:50:02.987
the money that has been
borrowed by the construction

00:50:02.987 --> 00:50:04.409
companies.
 

00:50:04.409 --> 00:50:08.510
So for instance,
Enel partner starts running

00:50:08.510 --> 00:50:13.208
into financial trouble,
it starts running into

00:50:13.208 --> 00:50:18.853
financial troubles that are so
big that probably the only

00:50:18.853 --> 00:50:23.190
security that he can give to the
banks,

00:50:23.190 --> 00:50:27.639
or renewing the loan that they
have extended to him,

00:50:27.639 --> 00:50:33.340
is the put of the 25% of Endesa
that he owns,

00:50:33.340 --> 00:50:38.739
or 25 point something to Enel.
 

00:50:38.739 --> 00:50:43.059
That put, by the way,
is at a price,

00:50:43.059 --> 00:50:48.489
that is the price of the bid,
which is 41.

00:50:48.489 --> 00:50:53.170
At the same time the price of
the Endesa shares of the market

00:50:53.170 --> 00:50:56.681
have gone down to 20 or 25,
between 20 and 25,

00:50:56.681 --> 00:50:59.099
but that doesn't mean much.
 

00:50:59.099 --> 00:51:04.722
Enel sees the opportunity to
get control of all of the Endesa

00:51:04.722 --> 00:51:07.217
shares,
approaches the entrepreneur and

00:51:07.217 --> 00:51:10.876
says,
okay you have the right of put

00:51:10.876 --> 00:51:14.014
for 2011,
why don't we negotiate a

00:51:14.014 --> 00:51:18.586
situation in which we would pay
you less than €31 per

00:51:18.586 --> 00:51:22.583
share,
you will get some assets,

00:51:22.583 --> 00:51:27.820
and we will get your 25% of the
shares,

00:51:27.820 --> 00:51:31.800
so there is an extensive
negotiation,

00:51:31.800 --> 00:51:38.829
and Enel ends up buying the 25%
of Acciona,

00:51:38.829 --> 00:51:44.088
dissolving the joint venture
and getting control of 92% of

00:51:44.088 --> 00:51:44.920
Endesa.
 

00:51:44.920 --> 00:51:48.518
However, you can see what this
does to Enel.

00:51:48.518 --> 00:51:54.510
The bid was largely based on
debt, the purchase;

00:51:54.510 --> 00:52:00.309
the accelerated purchase of the
shares has increased the debt,

00:52:00.309 --> 00:52:06.929
so now Enel finds itself with
$22 or $23 billion dollar market

00:52:06.929 --> 00:52:09.967
cap,
equity market cap of $65

00:52:09.967 --> 00:52:11.960
billion dollar debt.
 

00:52:11.960 --> 00:52:18.173
The change in--the change that
the management wanted has

00:52:18.173 --> 00:52:20.733
occurred,
but what happened is that

00:52:20.733 --> 00:52:22.710
because of the way that the
management,

00:52:22.710 --> 00:52:25.061
and because of the
circumstances,

00:52:25.061 --> 00:52:29.621
there is a huge load of debt on
the company and it is true that

00:52:29.621 --> 00:52:34.253
they wanted to have a more risky
company with a higher potential

00:52:34.253 --> 00:52:37.217
of goals,
but investors are not very

00:52:37.217 --> 00:52:41.550
happy about having invested in a
company in which the equity--

00:52:41.550 --> 00:52:46.268
the debt to equity ratio is
3:1, or 3.2:1.

00:52:46.268 --> 00:52:52.188
Enel thinks that a capital
increase in order to--a dividend

00:52:52.188 --> 00:52:55.760
reduction and a capital
increase.

00:52:55.760 --> 00:52:56.869
What is the problem?
 

00:52:56.869 --> 00:52:59.610
The problem is nothing,
probably there is enough room,

00:52:59.610 --> 00:53:01.590
we advise them,
there is enough room--

00:53:01.590 --> 00:53:05.530
there is enough appetite in the
market to do a capital decrease,

00:53:05.530 --> 00:53:10.349
but the problem is that the
Italian government directly

00:53:10.349 --> 00:53:14.934
through the treasury is--
holds 32% of Enel,

00:53:14.934 --> 00:53:18.998
and as you know,
these are not European and

00:53:18.998 --> 00:53:23.503
American governments these days
are saddled with a large amount

00:53:23.503 --> 00:53:26.409
of debt that they will have to
repay.

00:53:26.409 --> 00:53:30.626
So at the level of the Italian
government there is very little

00:53:30.626 --> 00:53:33.670
appetite for subscribing the
rights issue.

00:53:33.670 --> 00:53:37.123
On the other hand,
there is very little appetite

00:53:37.123 --> 00:53:41.900
for being diluted and make Enel
into a totally public company,

00:53:41.900 --> 00:53:44.179
because when you own more than
30%,

00:53:44.179 --> 00:53:45.849
according to Italian law more
or less,

00:53:45.849 --> 00:53:49.840
you nominate 100% of the board
or 90% of the board.

00:53:49.840 --> 00:53:55.889
There is the final effort by
the management is a negotiation,

00:53:55.889 --> 00:53:58.679
this time not with the Spanish
government,

00:53:58.679 --> 00:54:01.534
but with the Italian
government, in order to try to

00:54:01.534 --> 00:54:05.018
convince the government to let
the capital increase go forward

00:54:05.018 --> 00:54:07.360
and either be diluted or
subscribed,

00:54:07.360 --> 00:54:10.539
and this is not concerned to
the class,

00:54:10.539 --> 00:54:15.041
but the government eventually
gave up and found a way in which

00:54:15.041 --> 00:54:18.806
they could subscribe to the
capital increase without

00:54:18.806 --> 00:54:22.719
increasing the government
deficit of the country.

00:54:22.719 --> 00:54:26.135
Prof: Thanks Paolo,
we look forward to having you

00:54:26.135 --> 00:54:27.440
back in the Spring.
 

00:54:27.440 --> 00:54:33.000
 
 

